# Audit-stamp source-byte stability. The audit-stamp mechanism hashes the RAW source
# bytes of an audited module (validator/audit_stamp.py::compute_source_hash), so a shipped
# sibling stamp (`<module>.audit.toml`) is valid only if the audited file's bytes are
# identical everywhere the engine reads them — every dev checkout, the built wheel, and the
# public extraction repo. Under `core.autocrlf=true` a Windows checkout would rewrite the
# working-tree line endings to CRLF, diverging those bytes from the LF the repo stores, the
# Linux wheel build produces, and the natives' stamps are minted over. Pin the shipping
# source tree to LF so the source hash is platform-invariant.
src/conjured/**/*.py    text eol=lf
src/conjured/**/*.toml  text eol=lf
src/conjured/**/*.md    text eol=lf
